UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 AN ACT relating to pesticide labeling.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Any pesticide registered for use with the Department of Agriculture, pursuant to
6 KRS 217.570, or the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)
7 pursuant to the FIFRA as defined in Section 2 of this Act, and any regulations
8 promulgated thereunder, including but not limited to 40 C.F.R. pt. 156, that
9 displays a label that has been approved by the EPA in registering the pesticide or
10 is consistent with the most recent human health risk assessment performed under
11 the FIFRA shall be deemed a sufficient warning label for the purposes of an
12 action commenced under any provision of state law concerning the duty to warn
13 or label, or any other common law duty to warn.
14 (2) The provisions of this section shall not:
15 (a) Apply when a determination has been made by the EPA that a
16 manufacturer knowingly withheld, concealed, misrepresented, or destroyed
17 material information regarding the human health risks of such pesticide in
18 order to obtain or maintain approval of its label by the EPA; or
19 (b) Be interpreted to prohibit a cause of action based on any other provision or
20 doctrine of state law.
21 Section 2. KRS 217.544 is amended to read as follows:
22 As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
23 (1) "Active ingredient" means any ingredient which will prevent, destroy, repel,
24 control, or mitigate pests, or which will act as a plant regulator, defoliant, or
25 desiccant, or as a functioning agent in a spray adjuvant;
26 (2) "Adulterated" shall apply to any pesticide if its strength or purity falls below the
27 professed standard or quality as expressed on its labeling or under which it is sold,
