UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 or if any substance has been substituted wholly or in part for the pesticide, or if any
2 valuable constituent of the pesticide has been wholly or in part abstracted;
3 (3) "Animal" means all vertebrate and invertebrate species, including but not limited to
4 man and other mammals, birds, fish, and shellfish;
5 (4) "Antidote" means the most practical immediate treatment in case of poisoning and
6 includes first-aid treatment;
7 (5) "Board" means the Pesticide Advisory Board;
8 (6) "Defoliant" means any substance or mixture of substances intended to cause the
9 leaves or foliage to drop from a plant, with or without causing abscission;
10 (7) "Desiccant" means any substance or mixture of substances intended to artificially
11 accelerate the drying of plant tissue;
12 (8) "Device" means any instrument or contrivance other than a firearm which is
13 intended for trapping, destroying, repelling, or mitigating any pest or any other
14 form of plant or animal life other than man and other bacteria, virus, or other
15 microorganisms on or in living man or other living animals; but not including
16 equipment used for the application of pesticides when sold separately therefrom;
17 (9) "Distribute" means to offer for sale, hold for sale, sell, barter, ship, deliver for
18 shipment, or receive and, having received, deliver, or offer to deliver pesticides in
19 this state;
20 (10) "Environment" includes water, air, land, and all plants and man and other animals
21 living therein and the interrelationships which exist among these;
22 (11) "EPA" means the United States Environmental Protection Agency;
23 (12) "FIFRA" means the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide and Rodenticide Act as
24 amended, and any regulations promulgated thereunder;
25 (13) "Fungi" means all nonchlorophyll-bearing thallophytes; that is, all nonchlorophyll-
26 bearing plants of a lower order than mosses and liverworts, as for example, rusts,
27 smuts, mildews, molds, yeasts, bacteria, and viruses, except those on or in living
Page 2 of 7
BR135700.100 - 1357 - XXXX 3/5/2026 3:56 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 man or other living animals, and except those in or on processed food, beverages, or
2 pharmaceuticals;
3 (14) "Highly toxic pesticide" means any pesticide determined to be highly toxic under
4 the authority of sec. 25(c)(2) of FIFRA or by the department under this chapter;
5 (15) "Imminent hazard" means a situation which exists when the continued use of a
6 pesticide would likely result in unreasonable adverse effects on the environment or
7 will involve unreasonable hazard to the survival of a species declared endangered
8 by the secretary of the United States Department of Interior under Pub. L. 91-135 of
9 the United States Congress;
10 (16) "Inert ingredient" means an ingredient which is not an active ingredient;
11 (17) "Ingredient statement" means a statement of the name and percentage of each active
12 ingredient together with the total percentage of the inert ingredients in the pesticide
13 and, when the pesticide contains arsenic in any form, a statement of the percentage
14 of total and water-soluble arsenic, each stated as elemental arsenic;
15 (18) "Insect" means any of the numerous small invertebrate animals generally having the
16 body more or less obviously segmented, for the most part belonging to the class
17 insecta, comprising six (6) legged, usually winged forms, as for example, beetles,
18 bugs, bees, flies, and to other allied classes of arthropods whose members are
19 wingless and usually have more than six (6) legs, as, for example, spiders, mites,
20 ticks, centipedes, and wood lice, also nematodes and other invertebrates which are
21 destructive, constitute a liability, and may be classed as pests;
22 (19) "Label" means the written, printed, or graphic matter on, or attached to, the
23 pesticide or device, or to any of its containers or wrappers;
24 (20) "Labeling" means the label and other written, printed, or graphic matter:
25 (a) On the pesticide or device, or any of its containers or wrappers;
26 (b) Accompanying the pesticide or device at any time or referring to it in any
27 other media used to disseminate information to the public; and
