UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 (c) To which reference is made on the label or in the literature accompanying the
2 pesticide or device, except when accurate nonmisleading reference is made to
3 current official publications of the United States Environmental Protection
4 Agency, the Departments of Agriculture and Interior, the Department of
5 Health, Education and Welfare, and other similar federal institutions, the
6 College of Agriculture, University of Kentucky, Kentucky Agricultural
7 Experiment Station, Cabinet for Health and Family Services, Energy and
8 Environment Cabinet, or other agencies of this state or other states when such
9 agencies are authorized by law to conduct research in the field of pesticides;
10 (21) "Land" means all land and water areas, including air space and all plants, animals,
11 structures, buildings, contrivances, and machinery appurtenant thereto, or situated
12 thereon, fixed or mobile, including any used for transportation;
13 (22) "Livestock" means cattle, sheep, swine, goats, horses, alpacas, llamas, buffaloes,
14 and any other animals of the bovine, ovine, porcine, caprine, equine, or camelid
15 species;
16 (23) "Misbranded" means a pesticide is misbranded if:
17 (a) Its labeling bears any statement, design, or graphic representation relative
18 thereto or to its ingredients which is false or misleading in any particular;
19 (b) It is an imitation of or is distributed under the name of another pesticide;
20 (c) The labeling accompanying it does not contain directions for use which are
21 necessary for effecting the purpose for which the product is intended and, if
22 complied with, together with any requirements imposed under section 3(d) of
23 FIFRA are adequate to protect health and the environment;
24 (d) The labeling does not contain a statement of the use classification under
25 which the product is registered by EPA;
26 (e) The label does not contain a warning or caution statement required[which
27 may be necessary and if complied with, together with any requirements
Page 4 of 7
BR135700.100 - 1357 - XXXX 3/5/2026 3:56 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 imposed] under section 3(d) of FIFRA[, is adequate to protect health and the
2 environment];
3 (f) The label does not bear an ingredient statement on that part of the immediate
4 container, and on the outside container or wrapper, if there be one, through
5 which the ingredient statement on the immediate container cannot be clearly
6 read, of the retail package which is presented or displayed under customary
7 conditions of the purchase; provided, that the ingredient statement may appear
8 prominently on another part of the container pursuant to section 2(q) 2(A) (i)
9 (ii) of FIFRA if the size and form of the container makes it impractical to
10 place it on that part of the retail package which is presented or displayed
11 under customary conditions of purchase;
12 (g) Any word, statement, or other information required by KRS 217.542 to
13 217.630 or FIFRA to appear on the label or labeling is not prominently placed
14 thereon with such conspicuousness, as compared to other words, statements,
15 designs, or graphic matter in the labeling, and in such terms as to render it
16 likely to be read and understood by the ordinary individual under customary
17 conditions of purchase and use;
18 (h) The label does not bear the name, brand, or trademark under which the
19 pesticide is distributed;
20 (i) The label does not bear the net weight or measure of the content;
21 (j) The label does not bear the name and address of the manufacturer, registrant,
22 or person for whom manufactured; and
23 (k) The label does not bear the EPA registration number assigned to each
24 establishment in which the product is produced and the EPA number assigned
25 to the pesticide, if required by regulation under FIFRA;
26 (24) "Nematode" means invertebrate animals of the phylum nemathelminthes and class
27 nematoda, that is, unsegmented round worms with elongated, fusiform, or sac-like
Page 5 of 7
BR135700.100 - 1357 - XXXX 3/5/2026 3:56 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 bodies covered with cuticle, and inhabiting soil, water, plants, or plant parts; may
2 also be called nemas or eelworms;
3 (25) "Person" means any individual, partnership, association, or any organized group of
4 persons whether incorporated or not;
5 (26) "Pest" means any insect, snail, slug, rodent, nematode, fungus, weed, and any other
6 form of plant or animal life, or virus, bacteria, or other microorganism, except
7 viruses, bacteria, or other microorganisms on or in living man or other living
8 animals, which is normally considered to be a pest, or which the department may
9 declare to be a pest;
10 (27) "Pesticide" means any substance or mixture of substances intended to prevent,
11 destroy, control, repel, attract, or mitigate any pest; any substance or mixture of
12 substances intended to be used as a plant regulator, defoliant, or desiccant; and any
13 substance or mixture of substances intended to be used as a spray adjuvant;
14 (28) "Plant regulator" means any substance or mixture of substances, intended through
15 physiological actions, to accelerate or retard the rate of growth or maturation, or to
16 otherwise alter the behavior of plants, but shall not include substances insofar as
17 they are intended to be used as plant nutrients, trace elements, nutritional chemicals,
18 plant inoculants, or soil amendments;
19 (29) "Protect health and the environment" means protection against any unreasonable
20 adverse effects on the environment;
21 (30) "Registrant" means a person who has registered any pesticide pursuant to the
22 provisions of KRS 217.542 to 217.630;
23 (31) "Restricted-use pesticide" means any pesticide classified for restricted use by the
24 administrator, EPA, or by regulation of the department;
25 (32) "Spray adjuvant" means any wetting agent, spreading agent, sticker, deposit builder,
26 adhesive, emulsifying agent, deflocculating agent, water modifier, or similar agent
27 intended to be used with any other pesticide as an aid to the application or to the
Page 6 of 7
BR135700.100 - 1357 - XXXX 3/5/2026 3:56 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1357
1 effect thereof, and which is in a package or container separate from that of the other
2 pesticide with which it is to be used;
3 (33) "Unreasonable adverse effects on the environment" means any unreasonable risk to
4 man or the environment, taking into account the economic, social, and
5 environmental costs and benefits of the use of any pesticide;
6 (34) "Weed" means any plant which grows where not wanted; and
7 (35) "Wildlife" means all living things that are neither human, domesticated, nor as
8 defined in KRS 217.542 to 217.630, pests, including but not limited to mammals,
9 birds, and aquatic life.
